com.colinalworth.celltable.columns.client
Interface DataConverter<M,C>

Type Parameters:
M - the type of data in the bean used to represent the row
C - the type of data that the Cell expects
All Known Implementing Classes:
DoubleConverter, IntegerConverter, NumberConverter
public interface DataConverter<M,C>

Allows Cell instances generated from Columns interfaces to accept a different datatype than the bean used in the CellTable provides. Designed to allow, along with the optional Class parameter of @Editable, complexity that some Column instances might require to still be provided without complicating creation of all columns.

Author:
colin
